Query 2: Find the total sales amount for each product 

SQL: 

SELECT p.product_id, p.product_name, SUM(oi.price * oi.quantity) AS total_sales 

FROM PRODUCT p 

LEFT JOIN ORDER_ITEM oi ON p.product_id = oi.product_id 

GROUP BY p.product_id, p.product_name 

ORDER BY total_sales DESC; 

Sample Output: 

+------------+------------------+-------------+ 

| product_id | product_name     | total_sales | 

+------------+------------------+-------------+ 

| 2001       | Rolex Submariner | 12900.00   | 

| 2002       | Omega Seamaster  | 10400.00   | 

| 2003       | TAG Heuer Carrera| 9600.00    | 

+------------+------------------+-------------+ 

Query 3: List all users who made a purchase in November 2025 

SQL: 

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_id, u.surname, u.firstname, u.email 

FROM USER u 

INNER JOIN `ORDER` o ON u.user_id = o.user_id 

WHERE YEAR(o.order_date) = 2025 AND MONTH(o.order_date) = 11; 

Sample Output: 

